// Atkinson Hyperlegible — TrueType (glyf) font bytes, base64-encoded, for jsPDF embedding.
//
// jsPDF's `addFileToVFS` accepts a base64 string and `addFont` registers it as
// a Unicode font so German umlauts (ä/ö/ü) and ß render as real glyphs — never
// WinAnsi mojibake or an "SS" substitution for ß. Vendored as a build asset so
// there is NO runtime network fetch (constitution: fully offline).
//
// Source: @fontsource/atkinson-hyperlegible@5.3.0 (latin-400-normal.woff2, decompressed to sfnt) — the same subset vendored on-screen in Phase 3
// License: SIL Open Font License 1.1 — see AtkinsonHyperlegible-OFL.txt
// Copyright 2020 Braille Institute of America, Inc.
//
// Regenerate: decompress the vendored woff2 / download the upstream TTF, then
// `Buffer.from(ttfBytes).toString('base64')`. Kept as base64 (not a raw .ttf +
// Vite `?url`) so `src/core/pdf` stays DOM-free and unit-testable in Node.
export const ATKINSON_HYPERLEGIBLE_REGULAR_TTF_BASE64 =
  '';
